name: SPECTACULAR Rainy Plane Spotting at Dublin Airport! Aer Lingus, Etihad, and more!
description:
A very special thank you to Jonathan Winton for making the trip over to Dublin for some spotting with me! This video wouldn't have been nearly as watchable had he not let me borrow his tripod for a few of the aircraft that day. Go check out his channel: https://www.youtube.com/flyhellas101

A few days after arriving from Calgary on the inaugural WestJet 787 flight, I met up with Jonathan to get a morning's worth of action at Dublin Airport before I left for a short side trip to Poland. The forecast was not at all promising, as you'll see it wasn't bad early in the morning, but it ended up pouring and we eventually gave in, but not before getting some amazing rain spray shots.

Our arrangement was that I could film the "less interesting" aircraft with his tripod, while I took photos of the things he wanted to film on his own. Having zero Aer Lingus footage on my channel until now, I was perfectly fine with that arrangement! Enjoy this special Irish plane spotting compilation.
